<p>All Art Majors (including freshmen who start in Winter and Spring semesters) are eligible to apply for a limited number of partial-tuition awards. &nbsp;Scholarships are for two semesters. &nbsp;Portfolio reviews are held once each year, with award being given the following calendar year. &nbsp;Each student needs to complete the application and turn in a portfolio by the due date. &nbsp;</p>
<p>For those freshmen who start in the Fall semester only, there will be a one-time, new student scholarship portfolio review held in July. To apply for this scholarship portfolios must be received by the Department of Art Office (Spori 316) by July 1, 2015 at 5:00 p.m. This will be a one semester award. &nbsp;Any subsequent scholarship applications will be in November as listed above.</p>
